<TITLE> HC rejects petition, clears way for PSCs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 28 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court dismissed a petition on Thursday, challenging the state's right to sign Production Sharing Contracts and clearing the way for the government to go ahead with oil, gas exploration deals with foreign companies. The bench of justices Anwarul Haque and HM Shamsuddin Chowdhury threw out the 12-year-old petition, on which a stay was ordered on signing any PSC-based deal for exploration of onshore blocks. Abdur Rezzak Khan was for the petitioner and Kamal Hossain represented state-run oil co Petrobangla. Additional attorney general Murad Reza stood for the government. bd
